{
  "stem": "21626.4",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And with her support, you know, the pains eased.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I didn't bring auntie with me purposely, because I didn't want her to see me suffering.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "She suffered.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "She had enough to suffer without that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Anyway, I stayed with her that night and telephoned auntie and asked her, could I stay the night?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She was coming the next day, because my parents had put some of our most precious possession with different people.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And you know-- and she knew exactly who had what, because my mother obviously had told her.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So-- and Marta and I, we slept in the same bed, and we talked through the night.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And her-- she had lost her sister in the war, but that was through natural causes.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And her mother made me my favorite meal which my mother used to make such splendidly-- which were dumplings, but fruit dumplings, you know, filled with fruit and covered in lashings of curd cheese, and runny butter, and sugar, and all the things one shouldn't eat today.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But-- so it was a sort of a bittersweet visit.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the next day, when auntie came, we went around the people who were given my mother's spare coats, and our bound books, and things like that.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And do you know?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Mother's best friend denied she'd ever had anything.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Yet she had a big extension built [LAUGHS] to her house with my parents' money.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And months later, I saw her walking the streets in my mother's fur coat.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But some of the people who were either our servants who worked for us, or worked in the office, or who were just, you know, ordinary poor folks, they gave everything, and would have given much, much more would we-- if we had-- if I had taken it.",
      "word_count": 48
    }
  ],
